  "response": "Ignoring someone you have feelings for, especially if they also like you, can be challenging and may not be the best approach. If you truly like her and she seems to have positive feelings for you, it might be more beneficial to communicate openly about your feelings instead of ignoring her. Building a relationship based on mutual interest and understanding is often healthier than playing games or trying to create distance. If you have specific reasons for wanting to keep your distance, it might be worth reflecting on those and considering how they might affect both of you in the long run.",
